model: Master Compressor Diving Chronograph GMT Navy SEALs
size:
JLC Q178T470 Tactical BlaBucklested Case and 



Pre-Owned Jaeger-LeCoultre Master Compressor Diver GMT Navy Seals (Q178T470) self-winding automatic watch, features a 46mm titanium case surrounding a black dial on a black leather strap with a titanium tang buckle. Functions include hours, minutes, seconds, date, GMT and chronograph. 



Description


Jaeger LeCoultre Master Compressor Men's watch. Limited of 1500 Navy Seals edition. Titanium case with a black leather strap. Uni-directional rotating ceramic bezel. Black dial with luminous hands and stick hour markers. Arabic numeral marks the 12 o'clock position. Minute markers around the outer rim. Dial Type: Analog. Luminescent hands and markers. Date display between 4 and 5 o'clock positions. Chronograph - three sub-dials displaying: 60 second, 30 minute and 12 hour. Automatic movement. Calibre 757 engine. Scratch resistant sapphire crystal. Solid case back. Case diameter: 46 mm. Round case shape. Tang clasp. Water resistant at 300 meters/ 1000 feet. Functions: chronograph, date, hour, minute, second. Luxury watch style. Watch label: Swiss Made. Jaeger LeCoultre Master Compressor Chronograph Titanium Men's Watch Q178T471

id: The Patek Philippe Aquanaut is an iconic sports watch. It’s also about the most comfortable watch a Lady can wear. The rubber strap is very soft
name: and the case is just the right size
price: neither too big nor too heavy as some sports watches are wont to be. The modified (more rounded) tonneau case shape sits on the wrist just right. The case is water resistant to 120 meters (400ft)
brand: making this a true sports watch and an excellent everyday timepiece.

id: Rose gold case measures 35mm diameter. Sapphire front and display back crystals and screw down crown. The bezel on this watch is uniquely shaped and a classic Patek design element set with 46 Diamonds.

name: sweep seconds hand
price: applied Arabic numbers (hour markers and numerals have luminous) and date window at 3 o’clock.

name: supple
price: conforming to the wrist for a perfect fit
brand: and outfitted with a steel double folding Patek Philippe deployant clasp. An easy to overlook detail is how perfectly the strap ends and the 18kt Rose Gold case begins – it is a seamless fit between these two parts. The strap is also big enough to fit The Incredible Hulk (up to about a 10 inch wrist).

ABOUT


This pre-owned Omega Speedmaster Reduced Mother of Pearl 3534.70 is in like new condition. The watch comes as a full set (undated warranty card), along with 12 months warranty from us.




All of our watches undergo a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition to meet our strict standards. Additionally, we check each watch against records to ensure authenticity and ownership status.




This very rare Speedy features a stunning mother of pearl dial that is decorated with over sized Arabic numerals and equipped with a chronograph complication. Surrounding the dial is an all stainless steel, fixed bezel that is engraved with a tachymetre scale. Interestingly so, the scale reads “tachymetre base 1000”, as did the original Speedmasters before production changed to it reading just “tachymetre”, like what we see on newer models. The watch is housed by a 39mm stainless steel case and is presented on a very unique stainless steel bracelet that is indented with vertical lined centre links – very desirable for collectors. All of which is powered by the Omega 3220 automatic movement.




Model wears watch on 7 ¼” wrist

ABOUT


This pre owned, Omega Speedmaster Day Date 3222.80 is in fair condition. The majority of signs of previous wear comes from the bezel and dial whereby there are some impressions dotted around the bezel. The dial is also showing scuffing to the hands and indices, as well as to the dial plate itself. All of which however are not very noticeable when the watch is on the wrist. Additionally, the original chronograph hand has been replaced for the red tipped one. The watch was serviced in August 2022 and comes as a full set (undated warranty card), with additional 1 year warranty from us.




This lovely Speedy features a blue dial that is equipped with a quick change day-date feature at the 12 o’clock position. Additionally the dial is fitted with a 24 hour sub-dial at the 9oclock position, with additional chronograph complication. A handsome blue bezel matches the colour of the dial to provide contrast throughout the watch and is decorated with a tachymetre scale. The case of the watch is 40mm and composed of stainless steel, with matching bracelet. All of which is powered by the Omega Calibre 3606 automatic movement.

This Oyster Perpetual Datejust 41 in Oystersteel and white gold features a bright blue, fluted dial and a Jubilee bracelet.


Fluted


The fluted is a graphic interpretation of an iconic Rolex design element: the bezel fluting found exclusively on some of the brand’s Classic watches.


Made from age-old materials, combined with cutting-edge technology, the fluted dial brings depth and sophistication to the timeless Datejust.


A Rolex signature


The Rolex fluted bezel is a mark of distinction. Originally, the fluting of the Oyster bezel had a functional purpose: it served to screw the bezel onto the case helping to ensure the waterproofness of the watch.


It was therefore identical to the fluting on the case back, which was also screwed onto the case for waterproofness, using specific Rolex tools. Over time, the fluting became an aesthetic element, a genuine Rolex signature feature. Today the fluted bezel is a mark of distinction, in gold on this Datejust 41.


A meeting of two metals


Gold is coveted for its lustre and nobility. Steel reinforces strength and reliability. Together, they harmoniously combine the best of their properties.


A true Rolex signature, Rolesor has featured on Rolex models since the early 1930s, and was trademarked as a name in 1933. It is one of the prominent pillars of the Oyster collection.


Supple and comfortable


The design, development and production of Rolex bracelets and clasps, as well as the stringent tests they face, involve advanced high technology.


And, as with all the components of the watch, aesthetic controls by the human eye guarantee impeccable beauty. The Jubilee, a supple and comfortable five-piece link metal bracelet, was designed and made especially for the launch of the Oyster Perpetual Datejust in 1945.





Features:


Model: Date-Just


Reference number: m126334-0002


Case material: White Rolesor - combination of Oystersteel and white gold


Case diameter: 41mm


Bracelet material: Oystersteel


Power: 70 Hours


Gender: Man


Movement: Perpetual, mechanical, self-winding


Movement/Caliber: 3235, Manufacture Rolex


Water resistance: Waterproof to 100 metres / 330 feet


Bracelet: Jubilee, five-piece links

size:
The OMEGA Speedmaster is one of world’s most iconic timepieces. Having been a part of all six lunar missions, the legendary chronograph is an impressive representation of the brand’s adventurous pioneering spirit.





Presented on a black leather strap, this platinum model houses the iconic OMEGA Calibre 321, a movement that has been reborn for today using original specifications. Wearers can view the calibre through the sapphire-crystal caseback of the 42 mm timepiece, which has been crafted from a special platinum alloy with the use of gold (Pt950Au20).





The design also includes a black ceramic bezel with a white enamel tachymeter scale. Most notable is the step dial in black onyx, which uses 18K white gold for the indexes, and most hands. The vintage OMEGA logo is in 18K white gold. The design is completed by three unique subdials formed from a lunar meteorite, the same used for the Speedmaster Apollo 11 50th Anniversary Limited Edition in Moonshine Gold.
